CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 24, 1959, pg. 18 reads: ""The Pause That Refreshes" - These boys and girls are doing what most of the young set will be doing this week-end - socializing. With the week's graduating and semester - break celebrations, this scene is probably a typical one of the coming parties and dances.  Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two young women wearing short sleeved dresses in foreground, with young men, possibly Jeff Woodruff, and possibly James "Moose" McCoy in center, standing in interior with pine boughs
